1
00:00:05,379 --> 00:00:07,650
(Episode 7)

2
00:00:20,629 --> 00:00:23,629
My goodness.
You're such an annoying priest.

3
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,730
How shall I hit you?

4
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:29,829
Have you ever heard of it?

5
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:32,200
Do you know capoeira?

6
00:00:33,170 --> 00:00:35,140
You can't attack me
when I'm changing, okay?

7
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:37,909
Watch carefully.

8
00:00:58,229 --> 00:01:01,399
Guys, we're all going to hell
after getting rid of the priest.

9
00:01:01,469 --> 00:01:02,670
Kill him.

10
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:03,700
Stop!

11
00:01:05,469 --> 00:01:06,540
What are you doing?

12
00:01:09,439 --> 00:01:10,810
Don't you know
what kind of a day today is?

13
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:13,650
Director Kim.
I was hit without any reason.

14
00:01:13,709 --> 00:01:15,010
How can I just leave him alone?

15
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:17,920
Get up already! Don't make a scene.

16
00:01:26,489 --> 00:01:27,790
You should leave for now.

17
00:01:28,290 --> 00:01:29,359
Move your hand.

18
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,200
I will if you tell me...

19
00:01:32,829 --> 00:01:33,930
you'll leave.

20
00:01:34,530 --> 00:01:36,370
I won't, so move your hand.

21
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:41,409
I'll make you leave
if you don't leave by yourself.

22
00:01:44,510 --> 00:01:45,579
Try it.

23
00:01:46,909 --> 00:01:50,049
We've got the clip inside,
so let's wrap up from here.

24
00:01:50,719 --> 00:01:52,019
We're going to shoot here.

25
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:01,329
You're just letting him go?

26
00:02:01,829 --> 00:02:04,430
Or what? Do you want to be
on the news for beating priest?

27
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:06,799
Of course.

28
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:09,400
I can be quite thoughtless.
Where are my socks?

29
00:02:20,139 --> 00:02:21,180
(Award Ceremony for Businessmen
Who Contributed to Gudam)

30
00:02:24,419 --> 00:02:25,419
The priest.

31
00:02:25,849 --> 00:02:27,349
He's just everywhere.

32
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:29,789
I agree with that.

33
00:02:29,919 --> 00:02:31,789
Mic Testing.

34
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,289
Mic Testing. 1, 2, 1, 2.

35
00:02:34,490 --> 00:02:35,930
Mic Testing.

36
00:02:36,189 --> 00:02:38,060
I came here to congratulate...

37
00:02:38,629 --> 00:02:42,830
Mr. Hwang as he's receiving
such an honorable award.

38
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,870
Let's all pray.

39
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,370
Dear Lord of grace and blessing.

40
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:52,039
I'm truly grateful
that we all are gathered here...

41
00:02:52,509 --> 00:02:54,509
to congratulate Mr. Hwang
and pray for him.

42
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:56,280
Thank you...

43
00:02:57,379 --> 00:02:59,719
for letting us have a buffet.

44
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:01,289
But I feel...

45
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:04,259
a strong presence...

46
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:09,490
of Satan.

47
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,139
I'm just a part-timer here.

48
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:29,909
Dear Saint Michael the Archangel,

49
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:34,419
please protect us from the fight
against power and violence.

50
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:37,319
Please protect us from...

51
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:40,689
the fight against the rulers
of this dark world...

52
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,330
and the evil spirits.

53
00:03:43,129 --> 00:03:45,030
All Satans must listen.

54
00:03:45,129 --> 00:03:46,460
- My gosh.
- Goodness.

55
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,710
The music suits you very well,
right?

56
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,750
Stop it already.

57
00:04:07,219 --> 00:04:09,120
Why are you repeating
the same song so many times?

58
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:11,219
You have so much money.

59
00:04:12,689 --> 00:04:14,830
You should have used
a better catering service.

60
00:04:15,229 --> 00:04:16,589
This doesn't even seem unfrozen.

61
00:04:17,329 --> 00:04:19,730
I've heard a lot about you.

62
00:04:21,029 --> 00:04:22,970
I heard you caused a lot of trouble
when you're a priest.

63
00:04:25,769 --> 00:04:26,870
Who are you, lady?

64
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:31,610
I'm the head of Gudam-gu,
Jeong Dong Ja.

65
00:04:32,709 --> 00:04:35,009
Seeing how you're
close with Mr. Hwang,

66
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:38,649
you must be on the evil side also.

67
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:40,050
What do you mean by that?

68
00:04:43,490 --> 00:04:46,319
Father, why are you
laughing like that?

69
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:50,759
Mr. Hwang.

70
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,569
It's you, right?

71
00:04:56,529 --> 00:04:57,540
It must be you.

72
00:04:58,769 --> 00:04:59,800
What are you accusing of me?

73
00:05:00,069 --> 00:05:02,139
You killed Father Lee...

74
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:06,209
and threw him off the cliff.

75
00:05:11,319 --> 00:05:12,620
Father.

76
00:05:13,949 --> 00:05:14,990
You should stop doing that.

77
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:17,389
What kind of nonsense
are you talking about?

78
00:05:17,389 --> 00:05:18,959
Then why did you try to take over...

79
00:05:18,959 --> 00:05:20,019
the church's orphanage
and welfare facility?

80
00:05:21,889 --> 00:05:22,990
Did you secretly...

81
00:05:23,129 --> 00:05:25,259
hide something in those two places?

82
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:29,069
(Awards Ceremony for Businessmen)

83
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:33,040
What's so wrong with
trying to do something good?

84
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:41,250
Do you even know what "good" means?

85
00:05:41,579 --> 00:05:44,480
That's enough. Do you not know
what kind of event this is?

86
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,750
Of course, I know.

87
00:05:46,149 --> 00:05:47,949
This event encourages people to do
bad things by giving out awards.

88
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:50,459
- Father.
- You are unbelievable.

89
00:05:51,389 --> 00:05:52,589
I told you not to cause trouble.

90
00:05:52,790 --> 00:05:54,860
What kind of trouble did I cause?

91
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,759
I came to bless the event and eat.

92
00:05:56,829 --> 00:05:58,100
Bless the event, my foot.

93
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,199
You obviously came to throw a fit.

94
00:06:01,129 --> 00:06:02,199
What are you doing?

95
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,709
- Hurry up and take him away.
- Pardon?

96
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:10,939
We don't exactly have any reason
to take him away.

97
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,480
- Right, sir?
- What?

98
00:06:13,379 --> 00:06:14,949
- You have a point.
- What do you mean you have no...

99
00:06:16,279 --> 00:06:17,949
- My gosh.
- Why are you...

100
00:06:18,649 --> 00:06:22,149
trying to ruin the mood
on such a good day like this?

101
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,220
It's just not right.

102
00:06:33,129 --> 00:06:34,170
A good day?

103
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:36,970
A good day?

104
00:06:43,410 --> 00:06:44,740
Let's see how long...

105
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,910
this good day is going to last.

106
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:55,050
By the way,

107
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,160
doesn't this event give out
any free gifts?

108
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,189
If you want free gifts, go to
a 70-year-old man's birthday party.

109
00:07:04,199 --> 00:07:05,829
You must feel very frustrated.

110
00:07:06,699 --> 00:07:08,829
You obviously want to ruin my life,
but you don't know how.

111
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,300
And there's nothing you can do.

112
00:07:10,569 --> 00:07:13,939
So did you come here to at least
run your mouth?

113
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:16,310
How is this going to
change anything?

114
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,379
It's not like the dead priest
is going to come back to life.

115
00:07:19,980 --> 00:07:21,180
Nothing will change.

116
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:26,149
You shouldn't mention the dead.

117
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:28,920
Do you think I brought him up
because I wanted to?

118
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,589
You're the one who started
the conversation.

119
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:34,759
Anyway, if you want to come at me,
you better be well-prepared.

120
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,199
I'll be more than welcome
to fight you. Let's keep eating.

121
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:48,670
(Award Ceremony for Businessmen
Who Contributed to Gudam)

122
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:02,649
Why did you have to come here?

123
00:08:02,819 --> 00:08:05,360
Father, one more strike,
and you're out.

124
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:07,790
You'll get arrested
if you cause trouble one more time.

125
00:08:07,790 --> 00:08:09,290
You won't be able to get out of it.

126
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,230
Are you worried about me?
Or are you just annoyed?

127
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:16,629
Gosh, why would I worry about you?
I'm just worried about my job.

128
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:18,500
You really should be careful,
Father.

129
00:08:18,899 --> 00:08:20,839
I feel like I'm walking on thin ice
every single day.

130
00:08:21,639 --> 00:08:22,910
I'm sorry.

131
00:08:23,269 --> 00:08:25,009
What about me?
Why aren't you apologizing to me?

132
00:08:25,779 --> 00:08:26,980
Father. Father...

133
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:29,110
I'm not even annoyed anymore.

134
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:34,850
(Suicide Case of Father Lee
of Gudam Church)

135
00:08:35,649 --> 00:08:36,820
Wrap up the case.

136
00:08:39,759 --> 00:08:40,789
Okay.

137
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:42,830
What's with the long face?

138
00:08:43,929 --> 00:08:46,200
- No, it's nothing.
- It doesn't seem like nothing.

139
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:49,600
I don't really feel comfortable
about terminating this case.

140
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,299
There's not a specific
reason for it.

141
00:08:51,539 --> 00:08:52,870
But how should I describe this?

142
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:57,440
It feels as if I forgot to wipe
my bottom after I took a poop.

143
00:08:57,740 --> 00:09:00,809
I feel like I chewed on a huge
lump of aluminum foil...

144
00:09:00,809 --> 00:09:03,179
while eating gimbap
that was wrapped in one.

145
00:09:03,179 --> 00:09:04,750
You're so annoying.

146
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:07,289
Just hurry up
and terminate the case.

147
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:08,919
Okay.

148
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,730
I'm so stressed.

149
00:09:18,259 --> 00:09:21,730
(Daebum Trading)

150
00:09:24,899 --> 00:09:26,039
Get out of my way.

151
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:31,710
Open it.

152
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:33,610
Hurry up and open it.

153
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:35,710
(Award for Businessmen
Who Contributed to Gudam)

154
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:36,779
"Award for Businessmen"?

155
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:40,149
What a joke.

156
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,220
(Daebum Trading)

157
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,159
Darn it!

158
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,220
I can't even kill that jerk.

159
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:49,190
If you give me orders,
I'll take care of it right away.

160
00:09:49,289 --> 00:09:50,559
Are you kidding me?

161
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,899
What good will come out of
killing a priest?

162
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,570
The whole world will know...

163
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:57,200
that I was the one who killed him.

164
00:09:58,139 --> 00:10:00,139
I'm sorry, sir.
I was too thoughtless.

165
00:10:00,909 --> 00:10:01,940
Gosh.

166
00:10:02,809 --> 00:10:04,980
I should've just killed him
from the get-go.

167
00:10:05,679 --> 00:10:07,509
What in the world is his identity?

168
00:10:07,909 --> 00:10:08,909
Hey.

169
00:10:09,649 --> 00:10:12,879
I want you to find out
when and where he was born...

170
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:14,750
and what he used to do in the past.
Do you understand?

171
00:10:14,919 --> 00:10:15,950
Yes, sir.

172
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,220
Get going.

173
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:30,600
(Coffee with milk and cream)

174
00:10:32,669 --> 00:10:33,840
(Coffee with milk and cream)

175
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,509
You obviously want to ruin my life,
but you don't know how.

176
00:10:43,710 --> 00:10:45,019
And there's nothing you can do.

177
00:10:45,149 --> 00:10:48,549
So did you come here to at least
run your mouth?

178
00:10:59,529 --> 00:11:01,200
- Father.
- Let me go!

179
00:11:01,330 --> 00:11:03,269
- I said, let me go!
- Please calm down.

180
00:11:04,139 --> 00:11:05,139
Let go of me.

181
00:11:07,769 --> 00:11:10,909
I know you're angry,
but please don't hurt yourself.

182
00:11:11,809 --> 00:11:13,879
I can't mortify Father Lee
even after his death.

183
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:17,110
What?

184
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:19,480
If we just end this
without finding out the truth,

185
00:11:21,419 --> 00:11:23,250
it'll be mortifying Father Lee
even after he died.

186
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:29,759
But I feel like
I'm not doing anything right.

187
00:11:30,259 --> 00:11:33,460
Don't think that way.
You're doing your best.

188
00:11:34,470 --> 00:11:35,500
No.

189
00:11:36,399 --> 00:11:38,169
We won't be able to
disclose anything like this.

190
00:11:38,970 --> 00:11:40,970
We need to pressure them a lot more.

191
00:11:42,269 --> 00:11:43,570
Don't try to fight all by yourself.

192
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:46,580
Both Sister Kim and I
are on your side.

193
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:49,480
And I'm sure the archdiocese
will help us out as well.

194
00:11:51,049 --> 00:11:52,149
Father.

195
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,950
- Excuse me, Father.
- Yes?

196
00:11:57,419 --> 00:11:58,919
You have a guest.

197
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:00,659
A guest?

198
00:12:01,659 --> 00:12:04,159
I'm sorry I can't be of great help.

199
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,960
I didn't expect anything,
so you don't need to be sorry.

200
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:10,730
I hope this doesn't cause
a misunderstanding.

201
00:12:11,370 --> 00:12:13,700
The archbishop thought about it
for a long time...

202
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,669
I'll trust that he did.

203
00:12:17,639 --> 00:12:19,009
But why are you here?

204
00:12:19,539 --> 00:12:22,080
We can't continue to leave
the provost position vacant.

205
00:12:22,509 --> 00:12:23,950
So we'd like Father Han...

206
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:25,419
to become the provost
of Gudam Church...

207
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:28,090
according to the Code of Canon Law.

208
00:12:29,049 --> 00:12:30,620
Okay. What?

209
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,860
Me? Why me?

210
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:38,200
We're just following the code.

211
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:42,169
But I'm not...
I don't know anything yet.

212
00:12:42,169 --> 00:12:44,169
Father Kim is more suitable
for the position than I am...

213
00:12:44,169 --> 00:12:46,539
I'm not part of this diocese, so
I'm not qualified for the position.

214
00:12:46,539 --> 00:12:47,639
He's right.

215
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:50,340
I know the church isn't exactly
in the best situation,

216
00:12:50,539 --> 00:12:51,879
but I hope you guide it
in the right direction.

217
00:13:02,389 --> 00:13:04,259
I'm so glad.

218
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:06,659
I'll finally be able
to feel at ease.

219
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,289
I really don't know anything.

220
00:13:08,289 --> 00:13:09,730
I'm not good enough
for the position.

221
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:12,429
No, you're more than qualified.
You can do it.

222
00:13:12,429 --> 00:13:13,460
You'll do great.

223
00:13:13,659 --> 00:13:15,399
You need to do well
so that I can leave at ease.

224
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:18,269
No, you must stay for a while.

225
00:13:18,769 --> 00:13:22,340
Father Kim needs to go back
to his diocese.

226
00:13:23,039 --> 00:13:24,179
Yes, I know.

227
00:13:25,409 --> 00:13:26,740
But not now.

228
00:13:27,879 --> 00:13:30,149
I'm sure everyone
will be really happy...

229
00:13:30,149 --> 00:13:34,190
when Father Han starts
holding the mass. Don't you agree?

230
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:37,250
The fact that I have to fill
Father Lee's shoes...

231
00:13:37,990 --> 00:13:39,720
is making me
feel extremely pressured.

232
00:13:40,289 --> 00:13:42,159
Can you at least hold the mass...

233
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:44,860
until the end of this month?

234
00:13:47,429 --> 00:13:48,429
Sure.

235
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,539
You should just do it yourself,
Father Han.

236
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:53,299
Why? I said I'll do it.

237
00:13:53,799 --> 00:13:57,580
Okay, fine. Do whatever you want.

238
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:00,840
Hallelujah, Hallelujah

239
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,309
I get that you're pressured.

240
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:04,279
But you need to
pull yourself together.

241
00:14:04,279 --> 00:14:09,419
Hallelujah

242
00:14:09,649 --> 00:14:12,320
Why can't you just do it yourself?

243
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:14,990
What? Again?

244
00:14:15,159 --> 00:14:17,659
But thankfully,
he didn't cause a mess today.

245
00:14:17,659 --> 00:14:20,159
He just left after he ate.

246
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:25,740
All my Gudam-gu acquaintances
are throwing a fit...

247
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:30,240
and asking me why I didn't send him
to jail when I had the chance.

248
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:33,909
I'm not trying to question
your decision.

249
00:14:35,279 --> 00:14:38,080
But I don't think your choice
was 100 percent correct.

250
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:40,450
Do you also admit?

251
00:14:41,620 --> 00:14:43,190
- I'm sorry, sir.
- You're sorry?

252
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:45,220
Okay.

253
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:48,029
Next time, just send him to jail...

254
00:14:48,029 --> 00:14:49,429
the moment he makes
the smallest mistake.

255
00:14:50,429 --> 00:14:51,429
Yes, sir.

256
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:04,169
(Chief Prosecutor, Kang Seok Tae)

257
00:15:08,279 --> 00:15:10,580
Gosh, really.
He doesn't listen to me at all.

258
00:15:11,049 --> 00:15:12,820
I'm sure he didn't listen to
his mom either.

259
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,389
I told him...

260
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:17,759
That punk.

261
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,070
Song Sac. Song Sac.

262
00:15:35,139 --> 00:15:36,509
Sit down. Sit down.

263
00:15:38,980 --> 00:15:42,149
The expiration date is over
by a minute now. You can eat this.

264
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:43,350
(The food has to be
disposed of in principle,)

265
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:44,519
(but sometimes
the employees eat it.)

266
00:15:44,519 --> 00:15:48,850
